					<item>
				<guid>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6014661#post-3816067</guid>
				<title>(no title)</title>
				<link>http://www.scpwiki.com/forum/t-6014661/scp-3359#post-3816067</link>
				<description></description>
				<pubDate>Mon, 28 May 2018 18:09:54 +0000</pubDate>
				<wikidot:authorName>RockTeethMothEyes</wikidot:authorName>				<wikidot:authorUserId>4022320</wikidot:authorUserId>				<content:encoded>
					<![CDATA[
						 <p>I really like the Egyptian myth premise. I think it ties the article together very neatly. I will admit to being lost in the description, but that could be attributed to my own inability to pay attention. :P</p> <p>The second interview log is my favorite piece of this article. It definitely melds well with &quot;cold not cruel&quot; Foundation. +1</p> <p>However, I am confused as to why Agent Mohamed willingly ate the food in the tomb. If they were aware of the effects of doing so, wouldn't they be more wary of it?</p> 
				 	]]>
				</content:encoded>							</item>
